# Design System — Usage Guidelines

This prototype uses **Tailwind CSS** with a small set of CSS custom properties (`--ds-*`). Follow this order before writing custom HTML or CSS:

1. **Tailwind utilities first** — spacing, color, typography, layout.
2. **Figma spec second** — for larger patterns not yet coded; see [`docs/figma.md`](../docs/figma.md).
3. **Custom CSS last resort** — layout-only rules or `@apply` in component CSS files.

---

## Setup

```jsx
// src/main.jsx — required global import
import "./index.css";
```

Tailwind is configured in `tailwind.config.js`:
- **Base:** `stone-50` backgrounds, `stone-900` primary text
- **Accent:** `terracotta` (`#C4704A`) — links, primary actions, focus rings
- **Font:** Plus Jakarta Sans (loaded in `index.html`)

---

## CSS custom properties (`--ds-*`)

Use when a value must be shared outside Tailwind class strings (e.g. inline styles, canvas, third-party widgets):

| What you need | Token |
|---------------|-------|
| Primary text | `var(--ds-text-primary)` |
| Secondary text | `var(--ds-text-secondary)` |
| Page background | `var(--ds-surface-background-primary)` |
| Card background | `var(--ds-surface-background-secondary)` |
| Dividers | `var(--ds-border-divider)` |
| Interactive / links | `var(--ds-interactive-primary)` |

Define new `--ds-*` tokens in `src/index.css` under `:root` when needed — never hardcode brand hex in component CSS.

---

## Typography

Use **semantic HTML** with Tailwind classes. Do not set `font-size`, `font-weight`, or `line-height` in custom CSS for UI text.

| Role | Element | Tailwind (example) |
|------|---------|-------------------|
| Page title | `h1` | `text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900` |
| Section / card title | `h2` | `text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900` |
| Body | `p` | `text-base text-stone-900` |
| Secondary / meta | `p` or `span` | `text-sm text-stone-600` |
| Fine print | `p` | `text-xs text-stone-500` |
| Field label | `label` | `text-sm font-medium text-stone-700` |
| Link | `a` | `text-sm text-terracotta hover:text-terracotta/80` |

```jsx
// ✅ Page title
<h1 className="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900">Dashboard</h1>

// ❌ Never do this for UI text
<h1 style={{ fontSize: 24 }}>Dashboard</h1>
```

---

## Colors

**Never hardcode hex in CSS** for UI surfaces, text, or borders. Use Tailwind (`bg-stone-50`, `text-stone-900`, `border-stone-200`) or `var(--ds-*)`.

| Need | Tailwind |
|------|----------|
| Page background | `bg-stone-50` |
| Primary text | `text-stone-900` |
| Secondary text | `text-stone-600` |
| Accent / CTA | `bg-terracotta`, `text-terracotta` |
| Card surface | `bg-white border border-stone-200` |

---

## Buttons

Use consistent Tailwind patterns (or a shared component once you add one):

```jsx
// Primary
<button className="rounded-lg bg-terracotta px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-terracotta/90">
  Save
</button>

// Ghost
<button className="rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-stone-700 hover:bg-stone-100">
  Cancel
</button>
```

---

## Glass morphism

Use the custom utilities from `tailwind.config.js`:

- `.glass` — light frosted panel
- `.glass-strong` — stronger blur and opacity
- `.glass-panel` — subtle overlay panel

```jsx
<div className="glass rounded-xl p-6">...</div>
```

---

## Forms

Use native `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<select>` with Tailwind:

```jsx
<input
  className="w-full rounded-lg border border-stone-300 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder:text-stone-400 focus:border-terracotta focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-terracotta"
  aria-label="Full name"
/>
```

---

## CSS rules

1. **No `font-size`, `font-weight`, or `line-height` on text elements in custom CSS** — use Tailwind on the element.
2. **No `font-family` in component CSS** — inherits from `body` in `index.css`.
3. **No hardcoded hex** for UI color in CSS files.
4. **No broad selectors** that override Tailwind or shared components.
5. **CSS files are for layout** — `display`, `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, padding, margin, size, position; prefer `@apply` for repeated layout clusters.

---

## What NOT to do

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do instead |
|----------|----------------|
| `color: #1a1a1a` in CSS | `text-stone-900` or `var(--ds-text-primary)` |
| `background: #fafafa` | `bg-stone-50` |
| Arbitrary `font-size` in CSS | Tailwind text utilities on the element |
| Private npm design-system packages | Tailwind + this repo's tokens |
